<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n50100c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n50" href="#n50100c">N50 (VI.B.37)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n50all.htm#n50100c"> 100(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> westman / papar</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Thus, when the Northmen first discovered Iceland (about the year 860), they found no population there; but on &ldquo;Papey,&rdquo; in &ldquo;Papyli,&rdquo; and several places in the east and south of the country, they found traces of &ldquo;<mark>Papar</mark>,&rdquo; or Christian priests, who had left behind them croziers, bells, and Irish books; whence they perceived that these priests were &ldquo;<mark>Westmen</mark>,&rdquo; or Irishmen; for just as the Irish called the Scandinavians &ldquo;Ostmen,&rdquo; because their home lay to the east of Ireland so also did the Scandinavians call the Irish &ldquo;Westmen.&rdquo; <small> J.J.A. Worsaae, <a name="JJAW2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JJAW2"><cite title="source">An Account of the Danes and Norwegians in England, Scotland and Ireland</cite></a> (1852) 332</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
